NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

Performance Requirements

NFR-1: Response Time
Description: The system should respond to user actions within acceptable time limits.
Criteria:
- Page load time: ≤ 2 seconds
- Login authentication: ≤ 1 second
- Cart operations: ≤ 1 second
Priority: High


Security Requirements

NFR-2: Authentication
Description: The system should allow access only to authenticated users.
Criteria:
- Users must log in with username and password
- Access is based on role (consumer/admin)
Priority: High

NFR-3: Data Protection
Description: The system should protect user data.
Criteria:
- Passwords are stored securely
- Users can access only their own data
Priority: High


Reliability Requirements

NFR-4: System Reliability
Description: The system should function correctly without errors.
Criteria:
- No data loss during operations
- Errors are handled properly
Priority: High


Data Integrity Requirements

NFR-5: Data Consistency
Description: The system must maintain consistent data.
Criteria:
- Stock updates correctly after orders
- No invalid values allowed
Priority: High


Scalability Requirements

NFR-6: Concurrent Users
Description: The system should support multiple users.
Criteria:
- At least 20 users simultaneously
Priority: Medium


Availability Requirements

NFR-7: System Availability
Description: The system should be available at all times.
Criteria:
- Minimal downtime
Priority: High
